sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects modification of the registry settings used for Internet Explorer and other Windows components that use these settings. An attacker can abuse this registry key to add a domain to the trusted sites Zone or insert javascript for persistence

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Credential Manager Access By Uncommon Application
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description:
Detects suspicious processes based on name and location that access the windows credential manager and vault.
Which can be a sign of credential stealing. Example case would be usage of mimikatz "dpapi::cred" function

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Access To Browser Credential Files By Uncommon Application
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description:
Detects file access requests to browser credential stores by uncommon processes.
Could indicate potential attempt of credential stealing.
Requires heavy baselining before usage
